Assuming <em data-effect="italics">x</em> &lt;&lt; 0.033 and solving the simplified equation yields<span data-type="newline"><br/></span>
</p><div data-type="equation" id="fs-idm73884976"><math display="block"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1.2</mn><mspace width="0.2em"/><mo>×</mo><mspace width="0.2em"/><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>−4</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1.2</mn><mspace width="0.2em"/><mo>×</mo><mspace width="0.2em"/><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>−4</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></div><p id="[redacted for uniqueness]"><span data-type="newline"><br/></span>
The ICE table defined <em data-effect="italics">x</em> as equal to the bicarbonate ion molarity and the hydronium ion molarity:<span data-type="newline"><br/></span>
</p><div data-type="equation" id="fs-idm57413264"><math display="block"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mrow><mtext>CO</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><mo stretchy="false">]</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0.033</mn><mspace width="0.2em"/><mi>M</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mrow><mtext>CO</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><mo stretchy="false">]</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0.033</mn><mspace width="0.2em"/><mi>M</mi></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></div><p id="[redacted for uniqueness]"><span data-type="newline"><br/></span>
</p><div data-type="equation" id="fs-idp20713136"><math display="block"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mtext>O</mtext><mtext>+</mtext></msup><mo stretchy="false">]</mo><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msub><mrow><mtext>HCO</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mrow/><mtext>−</mtext></msup><mo stretchy="false">]</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>1.2</mn><mspace width="0.2em"/><mo>×</mo><mspace width="0.2em"/><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>−4</mn></mrow></msup><mspace width="0.2em"/><mi>M</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mtext>O</mtext><mtext>+</mtext></msup><mo stretchy="false">]</mo><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msub><mrow><mtext>HCO</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mrow/><mtext>−</mtext></msup><mo stretchy="false">]</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>1.2</mn><mspace width="0.2em"/><mo>×</mo><mspace width="0.2em"/><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>−4</mn></mrow></msup><mspace width="0.2em"/><mi>M</mi></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></div>
<p id="fs-idm162694608">Using the bicarbonate ion concentration computed above, the second ionization is subjected to a similar equilibrium calculation:</p>
<div data-type="equation" id="fs-idp103313952"><math display="block"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>HCO</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mrow/><mtext>−</mtext></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>q</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>+</mo><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>2</mn></msub><mtext>O</mtext><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>l</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo stretchy="false">⇌</mo><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mtext>O</mtext><mtext>+</mtext></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>q</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>+</mo><msub><mrow><mtext>CO</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mrow/><mrow><mn>2−</mn></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>q</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>HCO</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mrow/><mtext>−</mtext></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>q</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>+</mo><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>2</mn></msub><mtext>O</mtext><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>l</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo stretchy="false">⇌</mo><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mtext>O</mtext><mtext>+</mtext></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>q</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>+</mo><msub><mrow><mtext>CO</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mrow/><mrow><mn>2−</mn></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>q</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></div>
<div data-type="equation" id="fs-idm27760608"><math display="block"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msub><mi>K</mi><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>HCO</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mrow/><mtext>−</mtext></msup></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mtext>O</mtext><mtext>+</mtext></msup><mo stretchy="false">]</mo><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msub><mrow><mtext>CO</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mrow/><mrow><mn>2−</mn></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msub><mrow><mtext>HCO</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mrow/><mtext>−</mtext></msup><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow></mfrac><mspace width="0.2em"/><mo>=</mo><mspace width="0.2em"/><mfrac><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mn>1.2</mn><mspace width="0.2em"/><mo>×</mo><mspace width="0.2em"/><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>−4</mn></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msub><mrow><mtext>CO</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mrow/><mrow><mn>2−</mn></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>1.2</mn><mspace width="0.2em"/><mo>×</mo><mspace width="0.2em"/><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>−4</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><msub><mi>K</mi><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>HCO</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mrow/><mtext>−</mtext></msup></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mtext>O</mtext><mtext>+</mtext></msup><mo stretchy="false">]</mo><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msub><mrow><mtext>CO</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mrow/><mrow><mn>2−</mn></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msub><mrow><mtext>HCO</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mrow/><mtext>−</mtext></msup><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow></mfrac><mspace width="0.2em"/><mo>=</mo><mspace width="0.2em"/><mfrac><mro